captions.text: [MUSIC PLAYING]
-Hi.
We're Brooklyn and Bailey.

And today since we got so many
requests to do this video,

we decided to do a
Christmas and birthday haul.

And I will warn you, we
are both kind of sick.

-I have like, the worse
like, cold/laryngitis.
I sound like a frog when I talk.

Warning-- it might get
annoying, but there's
nothing I can do about it.
-Yeah.

So if you can't understand
what we're saying, that's OK.

But we're gonna show you
all the stuff we got.

First up we received
these gifts from Santa.
I got Nike shoes.
-And I got Lulu Lemon pants.
They're like, black leggings.

I've been stealing my mom's
for so long, so I think

Santa go the clue and
got me some for myself.

-Next up, my parents gave
me these Converse boots.
They're kind of a new fashion.
And I love them.
They're so comfy.

-And they also gave us some
Nike shorts and exercise--

like exercise shorts
and exercise shirts.

You've been asking
for those too.

-Bailey actually gave me
this movie, The Proposal.
And I love it.
I was so excited when I got it.
It's one of my favorite movies.
-I knew she would love it.
-That was a good Christmas gift.

-Also we got mints
from our stockings.
Gum from our stockings.
-Pound Reese's.
Of course.
-I mean, we ask for those a lot.
So I'm glad we got those.
Also, some more gum.
We got a lot of gum and mints.

-And my friend gave me some more
Nike shorts, as you can tell.
-And we got book readers.
Our grandma gave us these.

And like, it's a
really good idea,

cause you know, we
always stay up at night

and read our books without
our parents knowing.

So this is the
perfect gift for us.
So we can read at night.
-My friend gave me this shirt.

And Bailey is wearing
the shirt that she got,
and the necklace she got.
-And the necklace.

-And it was really funny,
because they actually

matched the clothes
to our personality.
I thought that was so cute.
-My parents gave me a Baby Lips.

It's like a Chapstick,
it's called Doctor Rescue.

So it's like healing your
lips, or whatever it is.
I love this stuff.
It feels so good.

-It was really funny that
it was Doctor Rescue,

because my mom's
always complaining
about how chapped my lips are.
-So thank you, Mom.

-Another friend for my birthday
got me this little makeup

travel bag and a
headband to go with it.
And there's a bracelet.
-I think she made the headband.
I think she made the headband.
And that was really cool.

-And she gave me
this little bracelet.
-Oh, so cute.
-So cute.
-OK.

So Shelby from OwlBeTeen,
our friend for like, forever.
She crocheted, right?
Crocheted the headbands.
Oh, they're so cute.
-And comfy.
-Thank you.

-They keep your ears
warm in the cold.
-They're so cute.

-Next up, my friend actually
gave me soup waffles.

And all my Dutch
friends out there,

these are my favorite cookies,
in case you're wondering.
Oh, they're so good.
I love them so much.

As you can see, I've
already opened them.

-We also got Barnes
& Noble gift cards.

And if you guys
know us at all, you

know that that's like the best
present we got of all time,

so that we can go buy
our favorite books.

And then we also have iTunes
git cards, like, a ton of them.

My grandma, she always
gets us iTunes gift cards.

So we have birthday, birthday,
and Christmas, Christmas.

So now we can go fill up
all of our music and apps
and stuff from iTunes.

-I also got some Sinful
Colors nail polish.

It's Mint Apple,
that's the name of it.
And yes, it's very cute.
It's nice and sparkly.

One of my friends gave me
these no-dent rubber bands
for my birthday.

-They're really
good, because when

you go to school with
straightened hair,

and you don't want like,
rubber bands to make

a dent in your hair,
you can use these.
-Yeah.
-They're really nice.
-I use them all the time.
Just saying.

Next up, my parents gave
us this MacBook cover.
And it's from Speck.

And I was so excited to get
it, cause I love the color.

-We're always confusing
our computers for work.

Like our parents have on,
and the kids have one,
and then we have one for work.

So we just decided
to color-code them.
-Yeah.

My mom has a red one now,
and my dad has a black one.

-And then we can tell
who's computer is who now.

-My mom and dad gave us
the Sigma Essentials kit.
And mine is Make Me cool.
-Mine is Make Me Blush.

-And there are 12
brushes in here.
And I'm so excited to use them.
-They're so soft.
-Soft.

-And they're like,
really good quality.

I mean, we've been
asking for good brushes,

because we don't really have
like, good makeup brushes.

And these are like, the best
we could have asked for.
-Yeah.
I'm so excited to use them.

They're from Sigma,
in case you missed it.
So excited.

And while we're on
the makeup track,

we got new makeup
bags from my parents.

And mine is just this
cute, colorful one.
And Bailey's is--
-This gray flowered one.
-Yes.

And it fits our
personalities perfectly.

Another gift we received for our
birthday was from our parents,

but you cannot see it,
because it's a new bedroom.
-It's not like a new bedroom.
It's just redecorated and stuff.
Like, we wanted new decorations.
So that's what they gave us.
-It's so cute.

So look for an upcoming
video on a new bedroom tour.
You'll be so excited.
It's so cute.

We're so lucky, as you
can tell, we so spoiled.
We got all these gifts.

Thank you to everyone
who gave them to us.

For all the calls and the
birthday wishes, and the gifts.
Thank you so much.

-All the information on the
stuff that we had in this video

will be in the
description box below.

-Be sure to comment
below on something
you got for Christmas.

And if you like this video, be
sure to give it a thumbs up.
-And happy New Year.
It's January 1, 2014.
-We are officially 14.
-The new year has started.
-Wow!
That went so fast.
OK.
Happy New Year, guys.
Bye.
-You wanna open yours?
-Wow!
-Look at that!
-These are my socks.
[MUSIC PLAYING]
-No pinching, Bailey.
No pinching!
[CHEERING]
